#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.169"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.169:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.169:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga"
msgstr "17. Resentment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.169:0.3"
msgid "169. Khippanisantisutta"
msgstr "169. Quick-witted"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.169:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged "
"greetings with him."

#. VAR: sāraṇīyaṃ → sārāṇīyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.169:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.169:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu khippanisanti ca hoti, kusalesu "
"dhammesu suggahitaggāhī ca, bahuñca gaṇhāti, gahitañcassa nappamussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, how are we to define a mendicant who is quick-witted "
"when it comes to skillful principles, who learns well, learns much, and does "
"not forget what they’ve learned?”"

msgctxt "an5.169:2.2"
msgid "“Āyasmā kho ānando bahussuto."
msgstr "“Well, Venerable Ānanda, you’re very learned."

msgctxt "an5.169:2.3"
msgid "Paṭibhātu āyasmantaṃyeva ānandan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t you clarify this yourself?”"

msgctxt "an5.169:2.4"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso sāriputta, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Reverend Sāriputta, listen and pay close attention, I will "
"speak.”"

msgctxt "an5.169:2.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Sāriputta replied."

msgctxt "an5.169:2.6"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda said this:"

# See BB’s note on the readings for nirutti and byanjana, which I follow. Note too that Comm. reads nirutti, byanjana. It’s unusual to find the Burmese text reading against the Comm.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.169:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu atthakusalo ca hoti, dhammakusalo ca, "
"byañjanakusalo ca, niruttikusalo ca, pubbāparakusalo ca."
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a mendicant is skilled in the meaning, skilled in the teaching, "
"skilled in terminology, skilled in phrasing, and skilled in sequence."

msgctxt "an5.169:3.2"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu khippanisanti ca hoti kusalesu "
"dhammesu, suggahitaggāhī ca, bahuñca gaṇhāti, gahitañcassa nappamussatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That is how to define a mendicant who is quick-witted when it comes to "
"skillful principles, who learns well, learns much, and does not forget what "
"they’ve learned.”"

msgctxt "an5.169:3.3"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an5.169:3.4"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ āyasmatā ānandena."
msgstr "How well this was said by Venerable Ānanda!"

msgctxt "an5.169:3.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi ca mayaṃ pañcahi dhammehi samannāgataṃ āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dhārema:"
msgstr ""
"And we will remember Venerable Ānanda as someone who has these five "
"qualities:"

msgctxt "an5.169:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘āyasmā ānando atthakusalo dhammakusalo byañjanakusalo niruttikusalo "
"pubbāparakusalo’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Ānanda is skilled in the meaning, skilled in the teaching, skilled "
"in terminology, skilled in phrasing, and skilled in sequence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.169:3.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
